 as domestic servants are but three examples. They focus on women of both minority and dominant cultures and reflect the West's characteristically mixed population. Telling Tales challenges founding myths of the region and invites a retelling of the story of western Canadian colonization and settlement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh1 aBoutilier, Beverly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarter, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavanaugh, Catherine A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCavanaugh, Catherine A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFlett, Sherry Edmunds, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlippenstein, Frieda Esau, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangford, Nanci, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeger-Anderson, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcmanus, Sheila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPagh, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRutherdale, Myra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwyripa, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarne, Randi R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarne, Randi R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruy